description:
Meet seventeen-year-old Ginji Kusanagi. Things are going great for him; he's only in high school but he's on the eve of making his debut as a pro-boxer. He's also just met Minako Sasebo, the girl of his dreams. Unfortunately, Ginji has an accident and dies...and is then reincarnated into a penguin! Will love be able to bloom between a boxing perguin and a beautiful girl!?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: First Love
  • Chapter 2: Drifting
  • Chapter 3: Friends
  • Chapter 4: The Power Of Love
  • Chapter 5: What A Man's Gotta Do...
  • Chapter 6: The Wrong Attitude
  • Chapter 7: Minako, Where Are You?
name: Vol. 1

description:
A new female trainer, Iida, arrives at the Irie Aquarium, and soon proves to be a formidable rival for Ginji's affections! The competition between Iida and Minako reaches soggy new lows during a pool party contest to win a trip to the South Pole, home to numerous species of Gin-chan's brothers-in-wings. Iida's nefarious plan involves a girl in a paper bikini and osmosis...you do the math!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Coach Iida
  • Chapter 2: Brain vs. Groin
  • Chapter 3: White Lie
  • Chapter 4: I'll Show You A Real Man!
  • Chapter 5: The Night of Revenge
  • Chapter 6: Escape
  • Chapter 7: Water Melons
  • Chapter 8: Homesick
  • Chapter 9: Bonus Short Story: Double Lesson
name: Vol. 10

description:
With four volumes still to go, through a set of exceptional circumstances, Ginji is returned to his human form! Unfortunately, as a penguin, he was only wearing a tie and a coat of many feathers...Then, before Ginji can meet his beloved as his true self, he must rescue her from life-threatening danger!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Lost & Found
  • Chapter 2: Grandma, Get A Grip!
  • Chapter 3: Penguin Hunting Season!?
  • Chapter 4: Sudden First Kiss
  • Chapter 5: Chocolate
  • Chapter 6: A Missed Opportunity
  • Chapter 7: Not A Dream
  • Chapter 8: Is This My Destiny?
  • Chapter 9: Anomaly!?
name: Vol. 11

description:
Rival city! Ginji vies with Minako's friend Helen for the role of Minako's guardian and gets upstaged as a stunt bird for Mike the Genius Penguin; Ginji's boxing coach's granddaughter and Nana the one-ton-of-fun walrus compete with Minako for (respectively) Ginji and Gin-chan's affections; and a Ginji look-alike threatens to steal Minako from human Ginji, and penguin Gin-chan from Minako (for a light snack)! Will the rivalry ever end...!?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Demoted Knight
  • Chapter 2: She Has Her Reasons
  • Chapter 3: Encounter
  • Chapter 4: A Star Is Born
  • Chapter 5: Summer Love
  • Chapter 6: Animal Out Of Control
  • Chapter 7: Train Ride From Hell!
  • Chapter 8: A Girl's Best Friend
  • Chapter 9: Just The Two Of Us...
  • Chapter 10: How Do I Look...?
name: Vol. 13

description:
Summertime means beaches, girls in bikinis, and penguins on the loose! But all this fun isn't without its consequences. Poor Gin-chan discovers that he's just fathered an egg. Ginji claims innocence because he's still unfamiliar with his own penguin plumbing, but how's Minako going to feel about her two-timing penguin?!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Selling Popsicles!!
  • Chapter 2: Humans
  • Chapter 3: A Most Memorable Lure
  • Chapter 4: I Shall Return
  • Chapter 5: After The Festival
  • Chapter 6: Flight!
  • Chapter 7: All About Penguins
  • Chapter 8: The Mystery Egg
  • Chapter 9: Eyewitness...
name: Vol. 3

description:
Ginji Kusanagi "dies" but in order to stay close to Manako, his one true love, he comes back to life reincarnated as an Adelie penguin. If that's true, then how could Ginji have fathered an egg with pretty little penguin, Linda?! Minako doesn't seem to mind, but Ginji doesn't know how this could have happened. After all, he still doesn't know all the ins and outs of his own penguin plumbing. Does penguin parenthood mean that Gin's days as a footloose and fancy free single penguin are over?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: So Kind
  • Chapter 2: Illegitimate Child!!
  • Chapter 3: Farewell, Mike...
  • Chapter 4: First Kiss
  • Chapter 5: Miss Shirakawa High
  • Chapter 6: And The Winner Is...
  • Chapter 7: Ginji's Back?!
  • Chapter 8: Reunion?!
  • Chapter 9: First Date
name: Vol. 4

description:
Ginji Kusanagi has died and gained his wings. Unfortunately, these wings don't fly--Ginji's been reborn as a penguin! Because of a bizarre loophole in the cycle of reincarnation, Ginji will be allowed to come back to life as himself as long as he lives out the natural life of a penguin. The reason Ginji's going through all this trouble is just so that he can be close to the love of his life, Minako Sasebo. Now Ginji must face the ups and downs of life as a kept penguin living in Japan. Unrequited love was never quite as unrequited as this!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Once Was A Boxer
  • Chapter 2: Pinky Ring
  • Chapter 3: A Penguin's Lifespan
  • Chapter 4: The Ceiling
  • Chapter 5: A Boss To Be Reckoned With
  • Chapter 6: Shinnosuke's Love
  • Chapter 7: Love Song
  • Chapter 8: A Woman's Intuition
  • Chapter 9: But... Still...
  • Bonus Feature: The Sasebo Home & Restaurant
name: Vol. 7

description:
Gin-chan the penguin plays cupid for a couple of kids in puppy love. And then, Gin-chan learns more about himself and his own predicament when he meets a kindred spirit in the form of an osprey who has also been reincarnated from a human!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Just For The Heck Of It
  • Chapter 2: Just As Much As Ginji...
  • Chapter 3: White Osprey
  • Chapter 4: It's A Curse!
  • Chapter 5: Completely Naked!
  • Chapter 6: Our Lady Of Heat Exhaustion
  • Chapter 7: Nan Da Na!!
  • Chapter 8: What Is... This Feeling?
  • Chapter 9: The Heartbreak Haunted House
  • Chapter 10: The Cause Of The Suntan
name: Vol. 8

description:
Gin-chan's hopes for a romantic island vacation with Minako are dashed when she meets a dead ringer for Ginji in his mammalian form. Should Gin-chan sabotage Minako's budding relationship with his doppelgänger when all Gin-chan has to offer is mackerel-breath pecks on the cheek? There's no time for closure on this moral dilemma when Minako becomes a damsel in distress yet again. Has she survived (in alphabetical order) abduction by boat and minivan, beauty pageants, falls, flirting, freezing, haunted houses, imposters, jealous rages, paper swimwear, peeping Toms, stabbing, strangulation, and tipsiness only to perish by water? Plus, meet another reincarnated soul, in the form of a cuddly koala. This seemingly innocuous critter has no natural predators, a two-yard long appendix, and gets nineteen hours of sleep a day...but now that he's come to Irie City, he's also got an appalling personal agenda!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Decision!!
  • Chapter 2: A Huge Mistake
  • Chapter 3: Renewed Determination!!
  • Chapter 4: From Despair To...
  • Chapter 5: Superstar Of The Land
  • Chapter 6: A Smooch ♥ And A Caress
  • Chapter 7: A Man's Worth...!!
  • Chapter 8: Speaking More Than Words...
  • Chapter 9: I Want Love!!
name: Vol. 14

description:
In the dramatic conclusion to Tuxedo Gin, the romantic comedy takes a serious turn. But first...heaven does its millennial spring cleaning, disrupting the supernatural process that traps Ginji's soul inside the body of a penguin. Just when Minako begins to figure out her pet's true identity, the man who murdered Ginji returns to add her to his list of victims! Now Ginji must decide whether to make the ultimate, permanent sacrifice to save the woman he loves...

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Stupid Men!!
  • Chapter 2: Tsutomu Yamaguchi
  • Chapter 3: Popo's First Love!?
  • Chapter 4: Up Close And Personal...!!
  • Chapter 5: Changing World
  • Chapter 6: The Shape Of Love
  • Chapter 7: He's Back...

description:
Break out the seaweed cigars--Ginji is a father! Or, more accurately, the reluctant guardian to a badly behaved fledgling penguin named Popo who has imprinted on him. In between rescuing bratty Popo from a fatal fate at the paws of a feline, Ginji is intent on rescuing Minako from the "love that cannot be named," and Mike the genius penguin from himself. But when Gin attempts to play peeping penguin at Minako and her friends' physical fitness exam, who will rescue him!?

Minako is finally reunited with Ginji! The only problem is that it's someone posing as Ginji trying to take advantage of Minako! What's a poor penguin to do? Can Gin-chan save Minako before it's too late?

description:
What's going on?! Gin-chan's hooked up with a super hot bikini-clad weather announcer and he's even been given the key to her apartment! Gin was reincarnated as a penguin so that he could stay close to Minako, but has he given her up for the sexy weather girl on TV?!

Things were going great for Ginji Kusanagi--Not only did he just make his debut as a pro boxer, he also just met the girl of his dreams, Minako Sasebo. Unfortunately, Ginji has an accident and dies...and is then reincarnated into a penguin! In this most silly or romantic love comedies, will love be able to bloom between a boxing penguin and a beautiful girl!?

description: Concluding the much-anticipated saga, this volume collects JLA #72-76, as the JLAers fight back from death to stop the Ancients from rewriting history. Aquaman has been found, but now he and the Atlanteans must be rescued. And in the present, the replacement JLA must also stop the Ancients while still learning how to function as a team.

description:
Those meddling kids are back on the case -- and this time they're in Egypt, helping to investigate the terrifying tombs of Tootincandy. The Mystery, Inc., gang has mummy madness to deal with -- and, of course, Shaggy and Scooby are nowhere to be seen!

Mummies beware, The Mystery, Inc., gang is back on the case...in Egypt. The gang must investigate the creepy tombs of Tootincandy - and, as always, Shaggy and Scooby are notably absent.
name: The Curse of Tootincandy's Tomb

description: Soulcatcher tells the story of a young, smart, and sexy widow who comes to the "the most haunted city in America," New Orleans, in search of the ghost of her dead husband. Instead she discovers she has the power to absorb the abilities of the recently dead, and uncovers a mystery the spirit world will kill to protect!
name: GN

description: The epic, untold love story between Marvel's two pre-eminent black super heroes - Storm and the Black Panther - is finally told, as only New York Times best-selling author Eric Jerome Dickey can do it! An orphaned street urchin, living by her wits on the unforgiving plains of Africa, struggles to harness her slowly developing mutant powers. A warrior Prince, embarking on his rite of passage as he ponders the great responsibility in his future. And a crew of ruthless mercenaries who'll stop at nothing to capture an elusive creature of legend: the fabled wind-rider. What sparks occur when their paths intersect? Don't miss out on this prelude to the wedding of Storm and the Black Panther!
name: Storm

description: Although it says "no. 5" on the cover, it is actually issue no. 1
name: Marge's Little Lulu and Tubby at Summer Camp

volume.name: Marge's Little Lulu and Tubby at Summer Camp

description:
Comic and cartoonist Scott Meyer is back with yet another book of bad advice wrapped in good intentions. Learn such important skills as How to Talk to a New Parent, How to Engage in Prefight Smack Talk, How to Complain about Work, How to Properly Perform a High Five, and more!

A former stand-up comedian, Meyer channels his extensive and varied wit into four panels of side-splitting culture commentary every other day or so and posts them to his website, basicinstructions.net. Our second collection of those Basic Instructions, Made with 90% Recycled Art, will likely spend some time on the copy machine before certain pages find themselves on cubicle walls worldwide.
name: Made with 90% Recycled Art
